markdown: △-HEATING IN OPEN AIR □-HEATING IN SEALED TUBE ○-HEATING IN NITROGEN ✗-AUTOCLAVING IN SEALED TUBE (120°C) <::Line graph showing the loss of thiamine over time. The y-axis is labeled "LOSS OF THIAMINE (%)" and ranges from 0 to 50. The x-axis is labeled "TIME IN MIN" and ranges from 0 to 30. There are four data series plotted: - One series, marked with 'x' symbols, shows a rapid increase in thiamine loss, starting from 0% at 0 min, reaching approximately 25% at 5 min, 40% at 15 min, and nearly 50% at 30 min. - Three other series, marked with 'o', 'triangle', and 'square' symbols, show a much slower and similar rate of thiamine loss. These series start at 0% at 0 min and gradually increase to approximately 12-15% at 30 min. The 'o' series reaches about 15% at 30 min, the 'triangle' series reaches about 13% at 30 min, and the 'square' series reaches about 12% at 30 min. : chart::>
